# GitHub - hookdeck/hookdeck-vercel: Authenticate, delay, filter, queue, throttle, and retry asynchronous HTTP requests (e.g., webhooks) made to a Vercel application via a middleware integration with Hookdeck
created: 2024-03-18, last updated: 2025-07-15, [Read more](https://github.com/hookdeck/hookdeck-vercel)

The Hookdeck Vercel Middleware adds the ability to authenticate, delay, filter, queue, throttle, and retry asynchronous HTTP requests (e.g., webhooks) made to a Vercel application.
...
const hookdeckConfig = {
match: {
'/api/webhooks': {
retry: {
strategy: RetryStrategy.Linear,
count: 5,
interval: 1 * 60 * 1000, // in milliseconds
},
rate: {
limit: 10,
period: DestinationRateLimitPeriod.Second,
},
},
},
};
...
- `delay`: the number of milliseconds to hold the event when it arrives at Hookdeck.
...
const hookdeckConfig = {
// vercel_url: '', // optional.
